1
00:00:08,375 --> 00:00:09,500
[NARRATOR]
The English emerged victorious

2
00:00:09,583 --> 00:00:11,458
from the bloody
Battle of Agincourt.

3
00:00:11,541 --> 00:00:13,208
From there,
they advanced on Paris,

4
00:00:13,291 --> 00:00:14,958
the capital of
the Kingdom of France,

5
00:00:15,041 --> 00:00:16,833
and captured the city.

6
00:00:16,916 --> 00:00:19,833
The French royal court
miraculously escaped the capital

7
00:00:19,916 --> 00:00:22,875
and relocated their palace
to the southwest, in Chinon.

8
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:24,583
Then, the Duchy of Burgundy

9
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:26,291
severed ties
with the royal family

10
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:28,458
and allied themselves
with the English army.

11
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:31,041
The entire region
descended into chaos.

12
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:32,791
With their fate hanging
in the balance,

13
00:00:32,875 --> 00:00:34,625
the people of France
suffered immensely,

14
00:00:34,708 --> 00:00:37,458
and their cries echoed through
every corner of the empire.

15
00:00:51,458 --> 00:00:52,541
[gasps]

16
00:00:53,708 --> 00:00:56,166
Miss Jeanne, what's wrong?

17
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:57,833
Are you all right?

18
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:07,291
I'm all right.

19
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:09,500
Don't worry, my friends.

20
00:01:09,583 --> 00:01:10,916
[FAIRIES gasp]

21
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,125
[JEANNE]
Hear my prayers.

22
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:54,625
May the English army
return to their own land.

23
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:56,916
[FAIRIES]
Go back to England!

24
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,333
And may this horrible war
come to an end.

25
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:01,875
[FAIRIES]
End this awful war.

26
00:03:01,958 --> 00:03:04,791
And, please, Lord,
let my body develop soon.

27
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:07,541
[FAIRIES]
May Jeanne become more womanly.

28
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:08,750
[FAIRIES gasp]

29
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:11,000
[screaming]

30
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:14,416
[FAIRY] This ritual has been in
the Fai Tribe for generations.

31
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:17,000
Have faith, your prayers
shall be answered.

32
00:03:17,083 --> 00:03:19,666
But it's done nothing to put
an end to the war so far.

33
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:21,625
And my breasts.

34
00:03:21,708 --> 00:03:23,166
[MAN]
There are people here already?

35
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:25,083
-[gasp]
-[screaming]

36
00:03:25,166 --> 00:03:26,416
Nothing to be frightened of.

37
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,125
I promise, I mean you no harm.

38
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:34,125
[JEANNE] Could you be
one of the black mages?

39
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:35,666
Ugh! Why would you think that?

40
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:38,625
I'm just a traveling alchemist.

41
00:03:38,708 --> 00:03:40,416
Montmorency.

42
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:43,666
If you don't mind,
we'll be using these ruins now.

43
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:44,833
[FAIRIES gasp]

44
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:46,750
[FAIRY 1]
Look, she's got wings.

45
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:48,125
[FAIRY 2] I'd heard
that only the queens

46
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:49,791
of fairy tribes have those.

47
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:51,916
Does this mean
she's a fairy queen?

48
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,250
[FAIRY 3]
Wait, but, I thought humans

49
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,041
couldn't tame fairies
with wings.

50
00:03:55,125 --> 00:03:58,458
Don't misunderstand, I have
tamed this human to be my slave,

51
00:03:58,541 --> 00:04:00,125
not the other way around.

52
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:12,625
Wow! This hat
you've got is enormous.

53
00:04:14,208 --> 00:04:15,250
Hmm?

54
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:17,875
Hey, you.
What are you even doing?

55
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,291
Is that a magical potion?

56
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,166
[grunts]

57
00:04:24,875 --> 00:04:26,416
[MONTMORENCY] If I can borrow
some of the power

58
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:27,833
present at these ruins,

59
00:04:27,916 --> 00:04:30,500
I may finally be able
to transmute the elixir.

60
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:34,541
Astaroth was right, as usual.
This might work.

61
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:35,458
[JEANNE]
Boobies.

62
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,458
-Huh?
-My boobies.

63
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:40,833
If I drink some of that potion,
will my boobs get bigger?

64
00:04:40,916 --> 00:04:42,208
[MONTMORENCY]
Not even a little.

65
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:44,125
But isn't it a magical potion?

66
00:04:44,208 --> 00:04:45,833
It is not magic.

67
00:04:45,916 --> 00:04:47,541
This is alchemy.

68
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:50,166
And for the record, it happens
to be quite a complex science.

69
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:52,250
-Oh, how about I help you, then?
-You'll just get in the way.

70
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,708
[JEANNE]
But I wanna help.

71
00:04:53,791 --> 00:04:55,041
[MONTMORENCY] Do you understand
what could happen

72
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:56,750
if the mixture is off,
even by a tiny bit?

73
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,750
All-out disaster.

74
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,000
Ugh! Moron.

75
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,500
[gasps]

76
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:05,000
[grunts]

77
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,583
[shrieks]

78
00:05:07,583 --> 00:05:09,250
[RICHEMONT]
Well, what are we waiting for?

79
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,541
[MONTMORENCY]
We solemnly swear...

80
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:12,083
[CHARLOTTE]
That no matter what...

81
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:14,583
[PHILIP] Even after we graduate
from the academy...

82
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:17,291
[ALL] We'll remain
best friends forever!

83
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:18,333
[gasps]

84
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:20,291
[bell tolling]

85
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:21,791
[MONTMORENCY grunts]

86
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,708
Well, it seems you didn't perish
from elixir intoxication.

87
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:28,958
Luck was on your side.

88
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:32,041
Did I fail again?

89
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:33,875
Yes.

90
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:35,041
[MONTMORENCY pounds]
Damn it.

91
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,416
Pathetic.

92
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,875
I thought that with my guidance,

93
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:39,833
surely you could manage
to transmute the elixir

94
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:41,666
successfully within three years.

95
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:43,083
But it's been seven.

96
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:44,333
That's more than twice the time

97
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:45,708
that it ever
should have taken me.

98
00:05:45,791 --> 00:05:47,333
The process requires
the transmuter

99
00:05:47,416 --> 00:05:49,000
to step into the unseen world,

100
00:05:49,083 --> 00:05:52,083
so naturally, the flow of time
will be altered a bit.

101
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,458
Hold on, you didn't even
realize that, did you?

102
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:56,000
What a loser.

103
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:58,166
I wasted the final years
of my childhood on this crap.

104
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:01,000
[sighs]
Listen well, Montmorency.

105
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:03,625
You have been chosen
to become the next Ulysses.

106
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,666
That means you will put an end
to the war on Earth forever,

107
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:09,333
including the Anglo-French War

108
00:06:09,416 --> 00:06:11,291
that's been raging
your entire life.

109
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:13,708
You will change the world
and create a utopia

110
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:15,791
that will last for eternity.

111
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,541
Do you understand
the magnitude of that?

112
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:20,791
It is the sole reason I bestowed
my knowledge unto you.

113
00:06:20,875 --> 00:06:23,958
So you had better get your act
together and deliver.

114
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:25,583
[grunts in frustration]

115
00:06:25,666 --> 00:06:28,750
Listen. I'm not doing this
to create some warless utopia

116
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:30,541
or to become
some legendary king,

117
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,541
so save
your motivational speeches.

118
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:34,416
You mean you have no ambition?

119
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,208
How disappointing.

120
00:06:36,291 --> 00:06:38,208
If you become king,
beauties will flock to you

121
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:39,458
like moths to a flame.

122
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:40,541
Not interested.

123
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:42,750
Ugh. Exactly what I'd expect

124
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,666
from a talentless virgin
like yourself.

125
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:47,333
Oh, that's rich, considering
you're primarily responsible

126
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:49,250
for my lack of
carnal knowledge.

127
00:06:50,708 --> 00:06:52,416
I'm so sorry.

128
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,625
It's my fault for getting
in your way, isn't it?

129
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:56,750
[sighs]

130
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:00,500
[MONTMORENCY]
It's not your fault at all.

131
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:04,166
I'm solely to blame
for my utter lack of talent.

132
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:05,916
So don't worry about it.

133
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:10,916
[gasps]

134
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,083
[voice breaking]
Thank you, Montmorency!

135
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:14,958
-[JEANNE crying]
-[MONTMORENCY] Oh, don't cry.

136
00:07:15,041 --> 00:07:16,541
Oh, please.

137
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:17,791
[bell tolling]

138
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,250
♪

139
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:22,291
[gunshot]

140
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:24,416
[villagers gasp]

141
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:27,708
My name is La Hire,

142
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:30,125
and I have come with a warning
that the Burgundian army

143
00:07:30,208 --> 00:07:32,500
is en route to lay siege
to this region.

144
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,458
Were you hired
by Princess Charlotte

145
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:36,125
to come to our defense
against them?

146
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:38,708
To protect our small village
from the attack?

147
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,333
-[LA HIRE] Yes.
-[villagers gasp]

148
00:07:40,416 --> 00:07:43,500
However, in exchange
for said protection,

149
00:07:43,583 --> 00:07:45,458
I'll need you to hand over
all your food.

150
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:47,375
[panting]

151
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:50,458
[gun cocks]

152
00:07:55,291 --> 00:07:56,583
[JEANNE]
Please, wait!

153
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:58,416
[LA HIRE]
A child?

154
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,250
[grunts]

155
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:02,041
[JEANNE] Don't hurt
these innocent people!

156
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:04,291
Spare them, pretty soldier.

157
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:05,583
[gasps]

158
00:08:06,666 --> 00:08:08,666
[MONTMORENCY panting]

159
00:08:09,625 --> 00:08:10,875
You're so reckless.

160
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,083
What would you have done

161
00:08:12,166 --> 00:08:13,375
if she had fired her gun
without warning?

162
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:14,375
[screams]

163
00:08:14,458 --> 00:08:16,125
And what's a black mage doing

164
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:17,833
in a remote village
like this one?

165
00:08:17,916 --> 00:08:19,458
No, you're mistaken!

166
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:22,458
[ASTAROTH] He's an alchemist,
not a black mage.

167
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:23,833
My eyes deceive me.

168
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:25,875
What is this
little flying creature?

169
00:08:25,958 --> 00:08:28,458
I didn't even know
winged fairies existed.

170
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:30,208
How can such a cute,
magical thing

171
00:08:30,291 --> 00:08:32,666
even be in this awful world?

172
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,416
This isn't good.

173
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,291
[JEANNE] But we can't
give you all the food.

174
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:45,333
How will we survive the winter?

175
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:47,541
You're getting paid
for your work, aren't you?

176
00:08:47,625 --> 00:08:49,000
Why don't you just
ask your employer

177
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:50,875
to increase your salaries?

178
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:53,541
We already have a hard time
getting our wages.

179
00:08:53,625 --> 00:08:56,500
I suspect that the royal family
has run out of funds in exile.

180
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:59,750
I'm sorry, but we can't
survive without money.

181
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,500
To protect you,
we'll need payment.

182
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:03,541
[JEANNE] Oh, I have an idea,
pretty soldier.

183
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:05,916
You could try surviving
on the fat stores in your boobs.

184
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,250
That'll last for months.

185
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,750
[LA HIRE] Shut up.
I am not a dairy cow.

186
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:11,500
Ah! That girl is so cute.

187
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:13,208
Are you sure
you're the same La Hire

188
00:09:13,291 --> 00:09:15,541
with a reputation for being
the biggest troublemaker

189
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:17,166
in the mercenary business?

190
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:19,166
Because I always pictured
a grumpy, old man

191
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:20,833
when I heard all the stories.

192
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:24,250
Oh, what's going on?

193
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,708
That's disgusting.

194
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:30,291
Was this guy
inappropriate with you?

195
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:31,416
Inappropriate how?

196
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,750
I'm a gentleman!

197
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,333
[ASTAROTH] Could that be
some sort of elixir?

198
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:35,291
What? You mean...

199
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:36,791
I see.

200
00:09:36,875 --> 00:09:39,041
You likely absorbed
a tremendous amount of elixir

201
00:09:39,125 --> 00:09:41,125
during that explosion
at the ruins,

202
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:43,166
and because of that,
you must have somehow

203
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:45,708
become a vessel
that can transmute it.

204
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:47,250
Is that even possible?

205
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:48,708
Theoretically, no,

206
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:51,000
but I struggle
to find another explanation.

207
00:09:51,083 --> 00:09:52,708
[LA HIRE] Hey, what are you two
talking about?

208
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:53,666
[BOTH]
Stay out of this.

209
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:54,916
[LA HIRE scoffs]

210
00:09:55,875 --> 00:09:57,041
[MONTMORENCY]
This is huge.

211
00:09:57,125 --> 00:09:58,500
So now my body can withstand

212
00:09:58,583 --> 00:09:59,958
swallowing
the Philosopher's Stone

213
00:10:00,041 --> 00:10:01,708
and I can become
the next Ulysses?

214
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:03,416
-[ASTAROTH] Yes.
-[MONTMORENCY] All right!

215
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:06,000
-One moment.
-[MONTMORENCY] Huh?

216
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,208
[ASTAROTH] It's likely that you
can only withstand being Ulysses

217
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:09,833
for three minutes at most.

218
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:11,791
Your body will continue
to transmute elixir,

219
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:13,416
which will react with the Stone,

220
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,958
causing it to become unstable
and spiral out of control.

221
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:18,708
[MONTMORENCY slurring]
Spiral out of control? How so?

222
00:10:18,791 --> 00:10:20,083
What will happen?

223
00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:21,458
[ASTAROTH]
I have no idea.

224
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:24,000
This whole thing
is unprecedented, even for me.

225
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:25,333
You may die of madness

226
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,333
as soon as the stone
takes over your mind,

227
00:10:27,416 --> 00:10:29,333
or, perhaps,
you might simply explode.

228
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:30,750
Whatever the case may be,

229
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,791
the consequences range
from bad to catastrophic.

230
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,041
[MONTMORENCY]
Oh, come on!

231
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:35,583
What the hell are you two
talking about?

232
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:36,791
[door opens]

233
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:39,583
[LA HIRE]
Xaintrailles, what's wrong?

234
00:10:39,666 --> 00:10:40,541
The enemy attacks.

235
00:10:40,625 --> 00:10:42,041
[LA HIRE]
That can't be.

236
00:10:42,125 --> 00:10:43,541
How did they get here so fast?

237
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:44,916
[XAINTRAILLES]
Why would I know that?

238
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:48,541
[XAINTRAILLES]
Here. Take this.

239
00:10:48,625 --> 00:10:49,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Heavy!

240
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:51,083
[grunts]

241
00:10:51,166 --> 00:10:53,083
[XAINTRAILLES] Your tiny sword
wouldn't slice a pear.

242
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:54,458
[LA HIRE]
Move out!

243
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,916
[JEANNE gasps]

244
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,541
-[SOLDIERS grunt]
-[shouting]

245
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:09,666
-[grunts]
-[groans]

246
00:11:11,875 --> 00:11:13,208
[grunting]

247
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,958
Whatever you do, don't let
them enter the village.

248
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:19,708
These sick bastards will burn
everything to the ground

249
00:11:19,791 --> 00:11:21,041
without a second thought.

250
00:11:26,083 --> 00:11:27,333
[VILLAGER]
If you can't wield a sword,

251
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:29,208
you could at least fight
with black magic.

252
00:11:29,291 --> 00:11:30,458
For the last time,

253
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:31,833
alchemy and magic
are different things.

254
00:11:31,916 --> 00:11:33,416
Hey, Astaroth.

255
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,500
What now?

256
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:35,916
I think I have an idea.

257
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,208
What if I pass the elixir
to La Hire by mouth?

258
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:39,666
Huh?

259
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,625
Then, if I let her swallow
the Philosopher's Stone,

260
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:43,416
she could beat these men
by herself.

261
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,833
Not a chance!

262
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:46,500
That woman is little more
than a glorified bandit.

263
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:49,416
If she obtains powers without
the capacity to master them,

264
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,791
it could make the situation
a thousand times worse.

265
00:11:51,875 --> 00:11:53,333
Ugh, you're dumber
than I thought.

266
00:11:53,416 --> 00:11:55,000
-[MONTMORENCY] Listen--
-[ASTAROTH] Absolutely not.

267
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:58,041
God in heaven, please protect
all these people from harm.

268
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,291
[FAIRY 1] We must find
a new safe haven quickly,

269
00:12:01,375 --> 00:12:03,958
before things get any worse!

270
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:05,541
[FAIRY 2]
Hmm.

271
00:12:05,625 --> 00:12:07,041
[FAIRY 1]
What are you stopping for?

272
00:12:07,125 --> 00:12:08,291
[FAIRY 3]
If you don't keep running,

273
00:12:08,375 --> 00:12:09,541
you'll surely be killed.

274
00:12:09,625 --> 00:12:11,000
But Jeanne is in danger.

275
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:13,583
[all gasping]

276
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:15,166
[groans]

277
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:19,416
We must not abandon Jeanne,
she's our friend!

278
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:20,541
[ALL]
That's right!

279
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:21,833
Hmm.

280
00:12:24,583 --> 00:12:26,708
-[FAIRY] Stop it, now!
-Huh?

281
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:30,125
Come on, let's work together
to save our friend's village!

282
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:31,833
[ALL]
Yeah!

283
00:12:31,916 --> 00:12:33,875
[SOLDIER] This tribe seems to be
made up of half-assed fairies

284
00:12:33,958 --> 00:12:36,291
who couldn't make it
to heaven or hell.

285
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:39,000
We exterminate creatures
like these on sight.

286
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:40,666
We won't let you do this!

287
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,333
[ALL]
Charge.

288
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:43,333
[gasps]

289
00:12:43,416 --> 00:12:44,458
My fairy friends.

290
00:12:44,541 --> 00:12:45,750
[ASTAROTH]
Frankly, I'm appalled.

291
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,458
Did you drool out
the last of your brains,

292
00:12:47,541 --> 00:12:48,958
slobbering like
a disgusting mongrel?

293
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:50,291
[MONTMORENCY]
What are you even saying?

294
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:51,666
[ASTAROTH]
That you're an idiot.

295
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,291
Oh, yeah? Well, you're
the size of a sparrow,

296
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:54,791
so it follows
that you'd have a bird brain.

297
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:56,291
[ASTAROTH]
How dare you?

298
00:12:56,375 --> 00:12:57,583
That's why you can't come up
with a solution to this.

299
00:12:57,666 --> 00:12:59,000
[JEANNE panting]

300
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:02,375
♪

301
00:13:08,416 --> 00:13:09,375
Huh?

302
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:12,375
[sobbing]
I beg you, human,

303
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:14,375
please don't burn down
Jeanne's village.

304
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:16,416
These people have done
nothing wrong.

305
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:17,708
Please don't.

306
00:13:17,791 --> 00:13:19,666
[SOLDIER]
I don't take orders from vermin

307
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:21,708
who think they have the right
to dress as humans!

308
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:23,791
-[SOLDIER stomps]
-How could you?

309
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:25,916
[gasps]

310
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:30,375
What kind of monster would kill
innocent little fairies?

311
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,083
-Why would you hurt them?
-[snickers]

312
00:13:34,166 --> 00:13:36,125
[ASTAROTH]
You continue to prove me right.

313
00:13:36,208 --> 00:13:37,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Hey, where's Jeanne?

314
00:13:37,625 --> 00:13:38,500
[gasps]

315
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:40,708
[JEANNE crying]

316
00:13:42,458 --> 00:13:43,958
[SOLDIER]
Let's make this quick.

317
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:45,583
We've wasted enough time.

318
00:13:45,666 --> 00:13:47,125
-[knife slashes]
-[gasps]

319
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:48,166
Done.

320
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,166
[JEANNE gasping]

321
00:13:57,875 --> 00:13:59,333
[footsteps approaching]

322
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:01,541
[MONTMORENCY]
No! She's been stabbed.

323
00:14:01,625 --> 00:14:03,083
I'm here, Jeanne.

324
00:14:03,166 --> 00:14:04,208
The ribbon.

325
00:14:04,291 --> 00:14:05,666
[MONTMORENCY]
Try to stay still.

326
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,333
[JEANNE]
But the ribbon...

327
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:09,583
[ASTAROTH]
I'll get it.

328
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:13,791
[JEANNE gasps]
It belonged to my sister.

329
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:17,291
Last year, the English army
came through in search of food,

330
00:14:17,375 --> 00:14:18,833
they pillaged our home.

331
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:20,833
They murdered my little sister.

332
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:22,791
[JEANNE sobbing]

333
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:25,375
Don't worry, Jeanne,
I can be your sister.

334
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:27,291
Hmm?

335
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:29,583
We'll be your family,
so don't be sad.

336
00:14:30,791 --> 00:14:32,625
[exhales]

337
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:33,708
[sniffles]

338
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:37,666
Ah!

339
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:39,000
[chuckling]

340
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,500
[JEANNE]
My whole life,

341
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:46,625
all I wanted was to be
a princess knight.

342
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:49,083
But they said
that only aristocrats

343
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:51,500
were allowed to have that job.

344
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:54,000
So, from then on,

345
00:14:54,083 --> 00:14:57,791
I tried to end the war
by using rituals instead.

346
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:59,458
Hmm.

347
00:14:59,541 --> 00:15:03,541
If only I had more power.

348
00:15:03,625 --> 00:15:06,666
[NICOLAS] To become more than
human carries enormous risk.

349
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:08,041
At the very least,

350
00:15:08,125 --> 00:15:10,458
it would mean banishment
from the church forever.

351
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:14,458
Furthermore, for all eternity,
one would always be on the run,

352
00:15:14,541 --> 00:15:17,375
living a solitary life,
without connection.

353
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,041
Jeanne.

354
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:21,750
If you truly wish
to go on living,

355
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:23,833
I can grant you
the power you need.

356
00:15:23,916 --> 00:15:24,875
[JEANNE gasps]

357
00:15:24,958 --> 00:15:26,125
You wouldn't.

358
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:27,583
[MONTMORENCY]
I would.

359
00:15:27,666 --> 00:15:29,208
If we allow her to swallow
the Philosopher's Stone,

360
00:15:29,291 --> 00:15:30,833
she'll be able to
assimilate its powers

361
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:32,083
and heal the wound herself.

362
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:33,750
It's too late for that!

363
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:36,000
[MONTMORENCY] What if we put it
directly into the wound?

364
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:37,833
-Would that work?
-Huh?

365
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:42,250
Is this the power you mentioned?

366
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:43,500
[MONTMORENCY]
Yes.

367
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:45,541
But, Jeanne, if you attain
this power,

368
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,708
you will no longer be human.

369
00:15:47,791 --> 00:15:49,666
You won't be able to stay
in this village.

370
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:52,333
[gasps]
I'd have to leave here?

371
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:54,416
But where would I go?

372
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:56,666
Does that mean I'd have
to be all alone?

373
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:59,416
[MONTMORENCY] No. I'll remain
by your side and protect you.

374
00:16:01,458 --> 00:16:05,125
From now on, until the day
you draw your final breath,

375
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:06,916
you'll never have to be alone.

376
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,541
[sighs heavily]

377
00:16:12,291 --> 00:16:13,375
Hmm.

378
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:19,708
[ASTAROTH]
I knew you were a fool,

379
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:21,041
you're a danger to us all.

380
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:22,625
You think it will work?

381
00:16:22,708 --> 00:16:24,083
This normal human girl,

382
00:16:24,166 --> 00:16:26,375
can she assimilate
half the Philosopher's Stone?

383
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:27,625
How should I know?

384
00:16:27,708 --> 00:16:29,166
No one has ever
attempted this before.

385
00:16:31,708 --> 00:16:32,833
[JEANNE groans]

386
00:16:32,916 --> 00:16:36,000
♪

387
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,458
What is this strange feeling?

388
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:53,375
Everything seems warm.

389
00:16:53,458 --> 00:16:54,833
It does.

390
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:57,166
That's the power of the elixir
moving between us.

391
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:00,125
[groaning]

392
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,416
[screams]

393
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,875
Stop! It's hurting!

394
00:17:03,958 --> 00:17:05,333
Fight through the pain!

395
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:07,916
I can't! It's killing me!

396
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,708
I can't stand it!

397
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:10,958
Make it stop!

398
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:12,166
[MONTMORENCY]
You're almost there.

399
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:14,708
-Keep fighting.
-It hurts!

400
00:17:14,791 --> 00:17:17,291
I want my mom!
Make it stop!

401
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:19,625
Just let me die
and be with my sister!

402
00:17:19,708 --> 00:17:21,541
Please just hang on!
Stay with me!

403
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:24,000
[JEANNE screaming]

404
00:17:25,583 --> 00:17:27,708
[LA HIRE breathing heavily]

405
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,500
Well...

406
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:32,041
since we're gonna die
how about a kiss?

407
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:34,125
[scoffs]
Over your dead body.

408
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:35,750
[SOLDIER laughs]

409
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:37,541
Made your peace with God?

410
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:40,000
[JEANNE] Are you prepared
to meet your maker?

411
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:42,375
-Oh!
-[SOLDIER 2] Who said that?

412
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:43,500
[LA HIRE]
Jeanne?

413
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:49,000
The girl from earlier.

414
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:50,750
You don't even have a weapon.

415
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:53,875
You really think you're a match
for trained mercenaries?

416
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:54,916
[gasps]
That's my sword!

417
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,625
[grunts]

418
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:02,250
[JEANNE] So, this is the power
of the Philosopher's Stone?

419
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:05,625
I feel its holy magic
welling up within me.

420
00:18:05,708 --> 00:18:07,166
If you're wise,
you will fear me.

421
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:10,791
I will make you weep
and beg for mercy.

422
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:11,875
My God.

423
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:13,625
What on earth happened to her?

424
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:16,083
♪

425
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:20,333
[grunts]

426
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:21,458
[groans]

427
00:18:29,083 --> 00:18:31,250
[laughs]

428
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:33,541
[JEANNE] You couldn't even
call this a battle.

429
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:37,041
Half-assed vermin who couldn't
make it into heaven or hell.

430
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:38,916
I'll exterminate you, vermin.

431
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,291
[SOLDIER]
She's a monster.

432
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:42,208
-Retreat!
-[SOLDIERS screaming]

433
00:18:42,291 --> 00:18:43,916
[MONTMORENCY]
Enough.

434
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:44,958
Stop this.

435
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,291
Show some mercy, Jeanne.

436
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:50,208
[LA HIRE] Hey! What the hell
happened to her?

437
00:18:50,291 --> 00:18:51,875
That's what I wanna know, too.

438
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:53,083
She turned into a devil.

439
00:18:53,166 --> 00:18:54,541
That's not the Jeanne
I recognize.

440
00:18:54,625 --> 00:18:56,958
[ASTAROTH] Once again,
you prove your ignorance.

441
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:58,791
It's the influence of the Stone.

442
00:18:58,875 --> 00:19:01,625
Its power
also intensifies emotion.

443
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:03,500
Don't worry,
humans don't have the fortitude

444
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:05,541
to maintain
the Ulysses frenzy long.

445
00:19:05,625 --> 00:19:08,791
Jeanne is just a girl and she
only assimilated half the Stone.

446
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:09,916
It won't be long.

447
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,416
You there, the dairy cow.

448
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,416
[LA HIRE]
Dairy cow?

449
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,416
I challenge you to a fight.

450
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,916
Killing meager soldiers
cannot satisfy me,

451
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,875
no matter how many
of them I defeat.

452
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,708
I crave a skirmish with a foe
at least as strong as you.

453
00:19:22,791 --> 00:19:24,333
All right, Jeanne,
that's enough.

454
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:25,791
-You shouldn't be--
-Hold on.

455
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:27,000
What's wrong?

456
00:19:27,083 --> 00:19:29,416
You're going to
get yourself killed.

457
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,958
[JEANNE] I've another reason
to fight you.

458
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:35,041
Those huge breasts of yours
are a terrible eyesore.

459
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:36,291
Keep your distance.

460
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:38,916
[VILLAGER]
Thank God you're safe!

461
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,416
[gasps]

462
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:42,125
Jeanne?

463
00:19:42,208 --> 00:19:44,291
Oh! She's been possessed.

464
00:19:44,375 --> 00:19:45,875
By the devil.

465
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:49,000
[JEANNE]
Right here.

466
00:19:49,083 --> 00:19:51,041
Aim for the head, please.

467
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:55,291
Even Ulysses couldn't survive
if you obliterate my brain.

468
00:19:55,375 --> 00:19:57,416
[LA HIRE] If I don't
kill her now, I'll be dead.

469
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:10,208
I knew you would take my advice
and aim for the head

470
00:20:10,291 --> 00:20:11,791
and that it wouldn't
even occur to you

471
00:20:11,875 --> 00:20:14,916
that your bullets are no match
for my lightning speed!

472
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,458
[LA HIRE] At least
I'll get killed by a cute girl,

473
00:20:17,541 --> 00:20:19,208
but that's not much consolation.

474
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:32,583
[moans]

475
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,375
The power ran out.

476
00:20:35,458 --> 00:20:37,541
-Good.
-Hmm?

477
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,333
Jeanne can only function
as Ulysses

478
00:20:39,416 --> 00:20:41,041
for three minutes at a time.

479
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:43,750
The power granted to her
is that of, "acceleration."

480
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:47,000
And the emotion intensified
is "arrogance."

481
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:49,375
[VILLAGERS chattering]

482
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:51,166
-[JEANNE] Mister Mayor.
-[VILLAGER] Hmm?

483
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,833
When my mother and father
come back,

484
00:20:52,916 --> 00:20:55,041
please explain
the situation to them.

485
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:59,750
Ugh! I don't even know where
to begin, how do I explain this?

486
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:02,000
How do I tell them
their daughter became a demon?

487
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:07,750
[sighs]

488
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,541
Well, the possibility
of eternal utopia

489
00:21:09,625 --> 00:21:11,125
just slipped further away.

490
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:14,416
So, Montmorency, where do you
intend to go from here?

491
00:21:15,375 --> 00:21:17,750
Sadly, Jeanne can never
return to this town.

492
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:20,166
Not only that, but she'll be
hunted down by the inquisition,

493
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:21,916
brutally tortured,
and executed.

494
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,458
-No, she won't.
-Huh?

495
00:21:23,541 --> 00:21:26,583
From this day on,
Jeanne will be known as a saint.

496
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:27,708
[LA HIRE]
A saint?

497
00:21:27,791 --> 00:21:29,208
How is that possible?

498
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:30,958
[scoffs]

499
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:32,000
Hmm?

500
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:34,416
♪

501
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:39,000
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne.

502
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:42,750
It's time for us to go.

503
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:51,333
[chuckles softly]

504
00:21:51,416 --> 00:21:52,791
Montmorency!

505
00:23:27,625 --> 00:23:28,791
[NARRATOR]
Just as there are

506
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:30,208
a myriad of face shapes
and hair styles,

507
00:23:30,291 --> 00:23:31,958
breasts are as unique
and varied as snowflakes.

508
00:23:32,041 --> 00:23:33,583
Some, like Jeanne's,
